Description: Handle sliver of a probably Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay medium-coarse light brown. Circular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 181, 35? No parallel known with a circular die.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1511)
